How to Spark Meaningful Conversations and Measure Success

    1. 1. HowtoSpark Meaningful Conversations andMeasure Success
       Publisher’s Pocket Guide
    2. 2. Your top 7 publishing questions, answered Alexandra Rynne
       Award-Winning Global Content Creator | Contributor, Social Media
       Examiner ... business.linkedin.com 109 Like Comment Share 659 views
       of your post in the feed 12 Comments Emotions have huge action
       potential and can enable consumers to receive messages they
       wouldn’t accurately perceive in another way, so if brands want to
       cut through the noise and optimize messaging to drive action ...see
       more What’s Trending: Emotional Connections in B2B Marketing 1mo
    3. 3. 1 LinkedIn members love to see creators like you giving your
       take on what’s happening in the news or your industry, whether it
       be through a post, a video, an article, or even a comment. This
       type of content resonates most with members, and helps you build a
       community of people with similar interests and professional
       insights. Don’t forget: Sharing your personal stories and
       experiences in a genuine way also inspires others. The more you can
       tap into existing conversations — whether around the office or in
       your industry — the more likely your article, post, or video will
       be successful. What should I write about? The best starting point
       is to respond to what’s happening in your industry or the
       professional world.
    4. 4. Should I post an article, a short-form post, or a video? Article
       Short-form post Video See LinkedIn’s guide for best practices for
       posting on LinkedIn for more details. Use articles to share your
       insights, perspectives, and expertise. Embed videos, images,
       slides, and more to strengthen your position. Use short-form posts
       to share and start conversations about what you’re reading, ask for
       advice or ideas, and respond to industry news, trending topics, and
       other major events. One of the easiest ways to start a conversation
       is to record a video. Consider using your smartphone for a more
       genuine look and feel. 2
    5. 5. How should I manage comments? Engaging in the comments of your
       article, post, or video can really make a difference. Responding to
       comments in a thoughtful manner is a great strategy to develop
       rapport with your followers and to build a community. 3 If needed,
       you can flag and hide abusive or offensive comments. Some effective
       ways to respond to commenters: “Hi XXX, I agree with your point!”
       “Hi XXX, thank you for your insightful comment. You are right that
       … ” “Hi XXX, that’s an interesting point. Can you elaborate on what
       you meant by xxx ... ”
    6. 6. How should I use hashtags in my posts? Use relevant hashtags to
       indicate what your post is about. Hashtags can be followed and are
       searchable, allowing your content to get discovered by LinkedIn
       members. You can start by taking advantage of the recommended
       hashtags at the bottom of your post editing window. 4
    7. 7. How do I track the performance of my content? Views in the feed
       Views Shares We recommend measuring success by the quality of
       conversations. While you can potentially get broad reach on
       LinkedIn, the real power is in the quality of the comments,
       feedback, and engagement from non-anonymous professionals across
       the globe. Write to reach the right world, not the whole world.
       Number of members who scrolled past your short-form post in their
       feeds. For videos, it includes any view of 3 seconds or more. For
       articles, it includes clicks from any source (on or off LinkedIn).
       For posts, it’s the number of times it has been shared on LinkedIn.
       For articles, it’s the number of times it has been shared on
       LinkedIn or another social platform. Learn more about the
       difference between post and article analytics. 5
    8. 8. How do I view analytics for my post? Click on the analytics icon
       below your posts to look at a detailed breakdown. Note: Your posts
       will display a detailed breakdown of the analytics only when they
       have been viewed by 10 or more unique viewers. Analytics on your
       posts are available for 60 days from creation. 6
    9. 9. How can I view analytics for my articles? Report this 3,115 810
       Comments Your articles will display a detailed breakdown of the
       analytics only when they have been viewed by 10 or more unique
       viewers. Analytics on your articles are available for two years
       from creation. You can click on the “View stats” button to look at
       a detailed breakdown. The number of views, likes, comments, and
       shares are displayed on the right side of the article. 7
   10. 10. Can I re-publish my LinkedIn content elsewhere, or vice versa?
       We want to publish articles from our LinkedIn Page. Can we do that?
       We are interested in sponsored content. Can you tell me more about
       what our options are? You can republish your writing from another
       publication on LinkedIn if you own the work or have the permission
       from the publication to do so. You retain ownership of all of the
       content that you post on LinkedIn and use on LinkedIn won’t
       restrict you from republishing those articles, posts or videos
       elsewhere. LinkedIn doesn’t currently support publishing articles
       from a LinkedIn Page. Instead, we encourage you to first write and
       publish from a personal profile. You can then re-share the
       published article by pasting the URL into the share box on your
       LinkedIn Page. If you are interested in sponsored content, you can
       set up a LinkedIn ad account. Learn more here. More content-related
       questions
   11. 11. For the first time in the history of media, you can reach the
       world’s professionals all in one place. More than 610M people
       worldwide gather on LinkedIn to stay connected and informed,
       advance their careers, and work smarter. Together they comprise the
       largest global community of business professionals. These are the
       decision-makers, influencers, and the leaders of today and
       tomorrow-precisely the people you want to target. For more
       information, visit marketing.linkedin.com. Subscribe to the blog
       for more expert publishing tips. Subscribe to the blog

